<br>
2 - Fire pets in PoA - nope.  Only air or epic pets.  Air end up with models that look like little blowup dolls (female efreeti).  Epic don't change their models.  Necro pets look like little purple wisps.<br>
<br>
1 - Bridge - basically this involves a parked necromancer on Isle seven.  He's one end of bridge.  Another character on Isle one is the other end of the bridge.  Everyone on the raid gets themselves killed by the keymaster and rezzed on Isle one, leaving a corpse available.  The two bridge &quot;anchors&quot; then shuffle everyone up to Isle seven by having the Isle one anchor be group lead and invite players into group for corpse summons.  Preferably the first two summoned up are a cleric and an enchanter.  Either necro then spends an EE to re-rez the cleric corpse (no further xp recovery, just summons the player up and puts them under rez effects), who then re-rezzes the entire raid force there.<br>
<br>
If you're on Druzzil, pitch me a tell - I've got a bridge set up with my own necro alt from when I went up to get my crown the first time.<br>
<br>
